This paper is primarily focused on face anti-spoofing, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques for feature extraction and classification, which makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the paper involves the creation of a 3D face attack database, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). As the paper deals with security and protection of face recognition systems, it could also be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of hypergraph representation for face recognition could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
